```
var a = ['1', '2', '3', '4']
a.map(parseInt)
(4) [1, NaN, NaN, NaN]
```
```
var returnInt = function(num){
  return parseInt(num, 10)
}
var a = ['1', '2', '3', '4']
a.map(returnInt)
(4) [1, 2, 3, 4]
```
```
['1', '2', '3'].map( str => parseInt(str) );

['1', '2', '3'].map(Number); // [1, 2, 3]

['1.1', '2.2e2', '3e300'].map(Number); // [1.1, 220, 3e+300]
```
